"11:5:16" : {s: 11, a: 5, w: 16, r: "", t: "إِنَّهُۥ", l: "إِنّ", lc: 1536, tl: "innahu", lb: "(জোর দিয়ে বলা) অবশ্যই, নিসন্দেহে",e: "Indeed, He", b: "নিশ্চই তিনি", f: 147, rm: ""},
"11:5:17" : {s: 11, a: 5, w: 17, r: "علم", t: "عَلِيمٌۢ", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "ʿalīmun", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী ",e: "(is) All-Knower", b: "মহাজ্ঞানী", f: 100, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
"11:5:18" : {s: 11, a: 5, w: 18, r: "", t: "بِذَاتِ", l: "ذُو", lc: 93, tl: "bithati", lb: "অধিকারী",e: "of what", b: "গুপ্ত বিষয়", f: 12, rm: ""},
"11:5:19" : {s: 11, a: 5, w: 19, r: "صدر", t: "ٱلصُّدُورِ", l: "صَدْر", lc: 44, tl: "l-ṣudūri", lb: "বক্ষ, সিনা, অন্তর",e: "(is in) the breasts", b: "অন্তরের", f: 15, rm: "To return from, come back, proceed, issue or emanate from, go forward, advance or promote, come to pass, happen, emanate from, strike on the chest/breast, commence. Anything that fronts, or faces one; hence breast, chest or bosom [often meaning his mind]. The fore part of anything. Going, or turning back and away."},
